 Audiotopia forges a new understanding of sound that will stoke debates about music, race, identity, and culture for many years to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMulticulturalismxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aMulticulturalismzUnited States. 0aMusicxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aMusicxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aPopular musicxHistory and criticismxUnited States. 0aPopular musiczUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Pop Vocal.2bisacsh  aamerica.  aamerican culture.  aamerican identity.  aamerican studies.  aart and music.  aartists.  abronx.  acritical analysis.  acultural studies.  adiscussion books.  aethnic demographic studies.  aethnic differences.  aethnic minorities.  ahavana.  ahip hop.  aklezmer.  alatin rock.  aliterary movements.  alos angeles.  amodern history.  amusic and culture.  amusic historians.  amusic history.  amusic lovers.  amusic studies.  amusic.  anonfiction.  apopular music.  arace issues.  aracial history.  aracial issues.  aretrospective.  aus borders.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093864940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938649423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938649/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles